    "about": {
        "paragraphs": [
            "Christina Perrier is a masterful writer and editor who values precision, accuracy, nuance, and style. Her expertise ranges from breaking news coverage to long-form feature writing, and everything in between, and spans print, digital, and social media formats. She is a passion-driven individual with a never-stop-learning attitude who thrives in collaborative spaces. Native to the newsroom, she is an efficient worker and natural leader in high-pressure, fast-paced environments.",
            "Christina earned a Bachelor of Arts degree in journalism from Lehigh University, where she graduated magna cum laude in 2023. While at Lehigh, she served as the editor-in-chief of The Brown and White, where she engaged in local, on-the-ground journalism that serviced the Lehigh and Bethlehem communities. She currently serves as InStyle magazine’s assistant editor; formerly, she worked as Harper’s Bazaar’s weekend news editor and has contributed to a number of other publications.",
            "The hats she dons are not confined to professional fashion. She is a music enthusiast, highly skilled in playlist curation but also devoted to the art of the album; a lover of literature, adept in setting ambitious reading goals; an experimental cook and mixologist, proficient in measuring with the heart (when appropriate); and a coffee connoisseur with a predilection for the French press and small cafés. She is a New York native, ambitious dreamer, and believer in kindness and compassion."
        ]
    },
